http://flutrackers.com

[The same province (Ogliastra, south east Sardinia) had reportedly been affected by BTV-1 earlier, in October 2012, with clinical disease in susceptible sheep (see ProMED-mail post 20121026.1367567). Since then, the disease has been reported in additional sheep flocks in south Sardinia. Their number, as of 6 Nov 2012 reached 14 confirmed outbreaks. A map, showing all outbreaks at that date, is available at http://www.izs-sardegna.it/foto_news/MappaBT.jpg.

With the addition of Sardinia, the SBV territories already occupy vast parts of Europe; the situation in the remaining parts remains to be uncovered by serological surveillance or by the appearance of malformed offspring in ruminants during the coming months, provided that such affected offspring be reported. - Mod.AS

Maps of Sardinia can be seen at http://www.solitalia.it/inc/images/province/sardegna-ogliastra.gif and http://healthmap.org/r/3VBw. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

